      • MAXIMUM_CHARACTERS

        public static final java.lang.String MAXIMUM_CHARACTERS
        Additional support header to allow user to customise the maximum characters can be sent. Unless this header is set, the default is 140 characters or if DATA_CODING header is set, the maximum character will be based on DataCodingSpecification.getMaxCharacters(byte). Setting this header manually may have unintended consequences.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • USE_MSG_PAYLOAD_PARAM

        public static final java.lang.String USE_MSG_PAYLOAD_PARAM
        Additional support header to send the sms using message_payload instead of setting using short_message. This can be used when we need to send long sms. (SPEC 3.2.3).

        Note:

        • That not many SMSC may support payload
        • The actual short message length which can be transmitted may vary according to the underlying network
        See Also:
